1
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:35,360
Don't sneak up on me like that.

2
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,560
That's not very nice.

3
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:39,840
<i>Did he take all the money?</i>

4
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,000
It's okay.

5
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:44,240
Because we've found a new target.

6
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:46,960
<i>She calls herself Goddess Hong Fa,</i>
<i>The Great Goddess.</i>

7
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:49,240
<i>It's just a plain old scam.</i>

8
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,440
<i>You need to go undercover,</i>
<i>earn the trust of these so-called mediums.</i>

9
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:55,720
Risa!

10
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,800
You really are my lucky charm!

11
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:01,600
I'll give you both the money in this bag

12
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,800
if you let me go.

13
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,920
That's how you catch the whole herd

14
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,840
without chasing after them.

15
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:12,880
But what they don't know is…

16
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:17,920
we've got another phone
that's identical to theirs

17
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Except this one

18
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,160
is linked to our bank account.

19
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:27,760
My advice? Don't set a screen lock.

20
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:30,720
If something comes up, anyone can use it.

21
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,280
So basically,

22
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:37,640
you're gonna swap our phone in

23
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:41,600
and trick them into transferring
all the money into our account?

24
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,840
Ris.

25
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:47,080
Just figure out how to swap
this phone with Gao's.

26
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,400
We'll handle the rest.

27
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:53,720
LIVE STREAM DAY

28
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:57,400
Don't use your nickname.
Use your real name. What's your name?

29
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,520
- Phorn.
- Phorn. Got it.

30
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:04,080
Sign here. Everyone, listen up.
Do a good job today.

31
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:07,120
Make it look natural.
If a lot of money comes in, big money,

32
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,760
I'll hand out bonuses. Sound good?

33
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,800
Yes!

34
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:12,000
- Good?
- Good!

35
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,160
Yeah, let's go.

36
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:16,720
YOUR NEXT PAYMENT IS ALMOST DUE
DEAR CUSTOMER

37
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:34,320
<i>Just figure out how to swap</i>
<i>this phone with Gao's.</i>

38
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,640
<i>We'll handle the rest.</i>

39
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,280
<i>I hope your plan works, Mungkorn.</i>

40
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,920
Alright, camera's ready. Hong, you ready?

41
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,920
Always ready.

42
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,720
You guys ready?

43
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,960
Ready!

44
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,520
Great.

45
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:04,480
Gao! Upstairs is ready.
How about downstairs?

46
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,440
Ready!

47
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,400
Let's do this!

48
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,760
I'm here. I'm connected.

49
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,760
Whoever seeks wealth

50
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,960
and prosperity,

51
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,880
believe in me,

52
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:23,280
<i>the Air-Drop Goddess!</i>

53
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:25,440
<i>Sathu.</i>

54
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:29,400
For this lottery draw,
three straight digits again, please.

55
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:32,560
Send your money

56
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,720
<i>by scanning the QR code.</i>

57
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,000
- GIVE ME THE LOTTERY NUMBERS
- WOW!

58
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,280
- HELLO
- SATHU 99

59
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,360
HURRY UP, I WANT THE LOTTERY NUMBERS

60
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,640
<i>Transfer it. Transfer it now.</i>

61
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,640
TRANSACTION SUCCESSFUL

62
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:48,280
The money's pouring in nonstop.

63
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:51,920
<i>Two thousand, 5,000, 7,000.</i>

64
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:55,840
More!

65
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,440
If you transfer this fast,

66
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:59,800
I'll give you ten more draws!

67
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,400
Oh wow!

68
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:07,120
We're rich! Filthy rich! Rich!

69
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:12,760
TRANSACTION SUCCESSFUL

70
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:18,840
<i>Sathu.</i>

71
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:22,160
<i>Sathu.</i>

72
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:27,120
Risa.

73
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:28,960
Yes?

74
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:32,440
Well, I wanted to talk to you
about something.

75
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:36,840
It's about the other day,

76
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,440
when you said there's a way
to win Hong's heart.

77
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,360
So what exactly

78
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,880
do I have to do

79
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:47,400
to make her notice me again?

80
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:50,480
Well…

81
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:59,200
I think you should sit down first.

82
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,680
Okay.

83
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:09,200
The way to win a girl over,

84
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:11,440
it starts with being attentive.

85
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:16,680
And I believe

86
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:18,880
you care about Hong

87
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,040
at least as much as Phayak does.

88
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,920
Really. The other day,

89
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,760
Hong actually complimented you to me.

90
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,680
Complimented me? What'd she say?

91
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,760
She said…

92
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,920
- What?
- That you're

93
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:40,840
kind, reliable.

94
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,640
And also,

95
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,480
you're a gentleman.

96
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,640
Considerate.

97
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,640
A leader.

98
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:56,240
I think you need

99
00:06:57,040 --> 00:07:01,480
to show that side of yourself
a little more.

100
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,680
A little more, huh?

101
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,920
So that means…

102
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:09,240
I still have a chance. I need to show Hong

103
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:11,320
more kindness and attention.

104
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:15,040
So she'll like me. Love me. Right?

105
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,080
Yes.

106
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:22,120
Up until now, I might've seen you

107
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:25,080
as a troublesome kid, suspicious and sly.

108
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,800
About earlier, I'm sorry.

109
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,200
Yes.

110
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,560
Just a little more!

111
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,360
Yak, you're done for.

112
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:36,480
Damn it!

113
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,600
<i>Not only do we need to understand</i>
<i>and keep up with these scams…</i>

114
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,680
<i>Another important question is,</i>

115
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:49,720
<i>how do we deal with these criminals?</i>

116
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,600
POLICE ARREST AIR-DROP GODDESS HONG
AFTER FINDING EVIDENCE OF DRUG TRAFFICKING

117
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,280
<i>Are scammers the same as criminals?</i>

118
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,240
<i>Not always.</i>

119
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,120
<i>The ones dumb enough to get caught,</i>
<i>those are the criminals.</i>

120
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,640
<i>Scams pulled off flawlessly</i>
<i>without ever getting caught,</i>

121
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,960
<i>that's skill.</i>

122
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:14,120
<i>And someone as skilled as me</i>

123
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,240
<i>could never be called a criminal.</i>

124
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:20,520
<i>But the more interesting question is,</i>

125
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,440
<i>how does the world decide</i>
<i>who's a good person?</i>

126
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,720
<i>It's much simpler than you think.</i>

127
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,240
<i>Just look at wealth.</i>

128
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,880
<i>Just by being rich, you can seem good,</i>

129
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:36,400
<i>honorable, and respectable</i>
<i>without even trying.</i>

130
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:52,440
<i>Wealth is a superpower</i>

131
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:54,000
<i>that lets you</i>

132
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,280
<i>win every game.</i>

133
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,800
<i>Sathu.</i>

134
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,080
- <i>Everyone stay calm!</i>
- <i>Sathu.</i>

135
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:10,920
- <i>The area is secured! Get out!</i>
- <i>Hey!</i>

136
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,920
- <i>Come on!</i>
- <i>What's going on?</i>

137
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,840
- <i>Hurry up!</i>
- <i>What?</i>

138
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,560
- <i>There's nothing here.</i>
- <i>Don't!</i>

139
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,240
- <i>Why are you arresting me?</i>
- <i>What? No!</i>

140
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,920
<i>- Stop!</i>
- Get out of here!

141
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:44,840
Risa! Come here, quick!

142
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,400
The cops are raiding us.

143
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,960
Gao, we're screwed. What do we do?

144
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,800
The money from Phayak's account,

145
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:53,120
we need to transfer it
to your mule account right now,

146
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,200
or the police will freeze everything.

147
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:58,080
Damn it. Yak's already been arrested.

148
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,920
Exactly. So what do we do now?

149
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,680
No worries. I'll handle this.

150
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:03,120
- Wait.
- What now?

151
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,480
Where's the backup phone?

152
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,120
The phone? Right here.

153
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,480
I'll handle it.

154
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,240
Wait.

155
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:21,240
A clumsy girl like you? You'll collapse
before you get there. I'll do it.

156
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:23,600
Alright then.

157
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:24,920
Hand it over.

158
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,760
Thanks for taking the risk.

159
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,560
Take care.

160
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:43,280
Could you not shove me? I'm handcuffed.

161
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,720
- Right.
- How am I supposed to run?

162
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,680
Officer, what did I do?
Why are you arresting me?

163
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:50,920
Exactly. We opened a spirit medium temple.
Is that illegal?

164
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,040
We're not here for that.

165
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:54,640
Wait. Not for that?
Then why are you arresting us?

166
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:57,120
We received a report
that you're dealing drugs.

167
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,280
- What?
- What? Drugs?

168
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:07,200
You've got the wrong people.

169
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:10,920
Drugs? How is that possible? I've never
touched the stuff. I don't have drugs.

170
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,160
Yeah, none.

171
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:15,200
Chief, we found drugs out back.

172
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,000
What drugs? Are you kidding me?

173
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:23,400
Take all of them to the station.

174
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,720
- Move!
- No way!

175
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:28,360
- You got the wrong people.
- I didn't do anything.

176
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,720
Easy. Be gentle. And show some respect.

177
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,840
I'm serious. Don't do that.

178
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:36,760
Don't touch me!

179
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,360
Done!

180
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:51,480
- What are you doing?
- Transferring money.

181
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,920
I was just checking the gold price
to see if it went up.

182
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,360
It went up today,
so I'm cashing out first.

183
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,640
Quit playing dumb.

184
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,680
- Come on.
- Sir, gold prices are up.

185
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,160
- To the station. Move.
- Up by 3,000 baht.

186
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,440
Talk at the station.

187
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:08,440
- Sir.
- Move.

188
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,840
How's it going? On plan?

189
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:28,080
Of course.

190
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,080
Perfect.

191
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:34,680
We're reporting them for drug dealing.

192
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,200
You think the police will believe us?

193
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:39,320
They will if we've got evidence.

194
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,000
How's it look?

195
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,520
Perfect.

196
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,720
We're rich!

197
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:11,080
Hey, Ris. You're incredible. Seriously.

198
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:14,240
I really admire you. If it were me,

199
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:17,120
surrounded by armed cops like that,

200
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,040
I'd probably piss myself.

201
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:28,120
Hey, Monkey! What kind of driving is this?

202
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,000
What?

203
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:35,080
MY ACCOUNT, AVAILABLE BALANCE
SAVINGS ACCOUNT

204
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,840
How is this possible?

205
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,160
What's wrong?

206
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,520
Why isn't the money in our account?

207
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,840
No way. I saw him scan it myself.

208
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:48,360
But nothing's showing up in the account.

209
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:55,400
Alright, let's head back
and check the CCTV at Hong's place.

210
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,200
Maybe we'll find something.

211
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,800
Here.

212
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:14,120
Let's fast-forward
to when they swapped phones.

213
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,480
See if anything looks off.

214
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,360
Everything looks normal.

215
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:24,480
Both phones are correct.

216
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:27,200
Phayak gave Gao the phone
with the red case.

217
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,800
And after the transfer,

218
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:32,280
did you check whether the money
went into the account?

219
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,080
What, Risa?

220
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:05,680
There he is. That's the cop
who bumped into me.

221
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,640
A cop?

222
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:10,520
Look at his hand.
He's reaching into my bag.

223
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:17,520
It had to be him switching the phones.

224
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:20,720
It has to be him.

225
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:24,880
How did he know about our phone-swap plan?

226
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,080
Exactly.

227
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,800
And the phones are the same model
with the same case.

228
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:34,560
Do you think those three
got busted by the cops?

229
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:37,640
Don't know.

230
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,680
By now, they've probably been arrested.

231
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:44,720
Can't be helped. They're just kids.

232
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,920
If you want to be a con artist,
this comes with the territory.

233
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:54,600
Five, one, seven! How is that possible?

234
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:57,440
Give it up

235
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,400
for the Air-Drop Medium!

236
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,680
Wow, amazing!

237
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:09,600
Of course it is.

238
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,360
If there's nothing else, I'm heading out.

239
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,560
A TOP-NOTCH LOTTERY NUMBER SOURCE
THESE STATS ARE AMAZING

240
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,880
<i>I've got to thank my instincts.</i>

241
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:28,000
<i>If I'd listened to that guy,</i>

242
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,480
<i>we would've needed</i>
<i>a way more complicated plan.</i>

243
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:33,480
Even that day,

244
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,560
I secretly sat there listening to them,

245
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:37,560
and they never noticed me.

246
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:38,800
<i>So basically…</i>

247
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:41,240
You're gonna swap our phone in

248
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:44,720
and trick them into transferring
all the money into our account

249
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,600
without them noticing, right?

250
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:47,720
Exactly.

251
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,120
Ris.

252
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,600
Just figure out
how to swap this phone with Gao's.

253
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,920
We'll handle the rest.

254
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:02,160
<i>Code 00. All units, standby for orders.</i>

255
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,120
24 HOURS EARLIER

256
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,119
Everyone stay calm!

257
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,400
- Sathu!
- The area is secured!

258
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,160
Don't you think
what we're doing is too harsh?

259
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,880
Those three are still kids.

260
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,960
If you're stepping into this world,

261
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:35,440
age and money don't matter.

262
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:41,160
Chen, the documentary I watched,

263
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:42,600
do you know how it ended?

264
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:45,640
Whoa, your documentary still isn't over?

265
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:48,040
That deer,

266
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:50,920
even if it fights off a pack of hyenas,

267
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,920
it'll still get killed
by something bigger.

268
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:56,560
What are you trying to say?

269
00:17:58,320 --> 00:17:59,680
The world works like that.

270
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,800
If you don't hunt, you get hunted.

271
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,640
If you want to win this game,

272
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,720
don't be the deer or the hyenas.

273
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,400
Be the predator

274
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:11,400
at the top of the food chain.

275
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:22,920
SUSPECTS: YAOWANAS POOLTHANYAPONG
CHALAKORN TORPOL, PHAYAK MILLER

276
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,480
Help!

277
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:26,800
The police are attacking civilians!

278
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:31,120
Framing innocent people like this, how
can you call yourselves law enforcement?

279
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,240
Okay, fine.

280
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,320
Step out.

281
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,600
Stop yelling.

282
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:37,680
What?

283
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:42,520
The investigation found
no evidence of wrongdoing.

284
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,760
As for the seized substance
suspected to be drugs,

285
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:48,400
the forensic report

286
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,520
says it was just…

287
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:52,840
flour.

288
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:53,840
See?

289
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:56,800
I told you. We didn't do anything wrong.

290
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,360
You framed us.

291
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:00,320
How are you going
to take responsibility for this?

292
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,880
Sue them, buddy. Sue them
till they've got nowhere to run.

293
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,760
If you want to sue, go ahead. But first,

294
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:09,000
can you hurry up?
You're so loud, I can't take it. Move.

295
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,880
- Are you planting something?
- Wait!

296
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:16,560
You're dirty. Don't touch us.
We have dignity.

297
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:18,320
- We can walk on our own.
- Stay away.

298
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,440
VISITING HOURS FOR SUSPECTS

299
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:21,600
Here's your stuff back.

300
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,280
Let's see.

301
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:28,080
This one's mine.

302
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:32,880
So many missed calls and messages.

303
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,280
Are those missed calls

304
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:37,600
from your followers?
They're probably cheering you on, Hong.

305
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:38,200
THE REPAYMENT WITH INTEREST IS DUE
IF YOU DON'T PAY, YOU'RE DEAD

306
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:38,840
MISSED CALL
BOSS KLUAY

307
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:41,800
Boss Kluay, I don't get it.
He's always hounding me for money.

308
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:43,880
- Gao.
- Yeah?

309
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,560
Hurry up and transfer all the money back.

310
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:48,800
I can't deal with this.
And don't contact him again.

311
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:49,960
- Whatever's left, it's fine.
- Okay.

312
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:51,920
- Crazy.
- I'll take care of it.

313
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:54,360
- Alright.
- Swipe.

314
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,320
Hey.

315
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,480
Why isn't it working?

316
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:03,800
- Do you remember the passcode?
- How could I forget?

317
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,800
It's my birthdate. Of course, I remember.

318
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,600
If you remember it,

319
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,320
then why won't it unlock?

320
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,960
You cavemen! Absolute cavemen!

321
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:14,760
Come here. I'll do it. Hong, calm down.

322
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,680
Don't worry. I've got this.

323
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,920
- Do it.
- I got it.

324
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,440
Just watch.

325
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:24,560
The phone's broken.

326
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:27,680
- Oh, Mr. IT! So, can you fix it or not?
- You broke the phone?

327
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,080
- I only pressed it once.
- You pressed it like ten times.

328
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,960
Enough!

329
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:33,200
It's easier to just call the bank.

330
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:36,560
I'm going to change clothes.
Hurry up and come with me.

331
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:39,400
Okay, got it. I'll handle it.

332
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:40,400
Yes.

333
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:45,000
Hello.

334
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,120
Are you Hong?

335
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,080
Who's this?

336
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,560
Please hold for a moment.

337
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:05,160
Boss, you've got a call.

338
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:08,240
Hey.

339
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:12,240
What's up?

340
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:15,240
I found Hong, boss. Got it.

341
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,200
Boss Kluay wants to talk to you.

342
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:20,840
I see. Kluay's thug.

343
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:23,840
Perfect timing. I'll give him a piece
of my mind, then transfer the money.

344
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,240
Hello.

345
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,040
Hey, Air-Drop Goddess.

346
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:36,320
I heard the three million
you borrowed is overdue.

347
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,200
Come on, boss.

348
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:41,400
I only borrowed a few million.
You keep nagging me.

349
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,600
<i>I'm not running off with your money.</i>
<i>You'll get it back.</i>

350
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:44,920
You're just a creditor,

351
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:48,000
not a call center calling to harass me
like some squawking bird.

352
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,560
<i>Don't you want your money back?</i>

353
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:54,200
And another thing. Remember this.
I'm a good customer.

354
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:58,280
I keep my word. Don't call me again, okay?
You're annoying.

355
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:01,120
You Boss Kluay! You crazy!

356
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:08,400
- Hong, listen.
- Don't do that.

357
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:10,200
What? I'm not done yelling at him yet.

358
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:11,480
Wait!

359
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:14,000
The money we transferred,
it didn't go into our account.

360
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:15,800
- Yeah.
- What? Then where did it go?

361
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,600
I don't know either,
but I followed every step.

362
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:21,200
- Every single step Risa told me to.
- Wait a second.

363
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:24,160
If there's no money, then…

364
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:29,320
All that yelling at Boss Kluay just now…

365
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,960
Excuse me.

366
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,920
You just said the money's gone missing.
Is there a problem?

367
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,280
No. Nothing at all.

368
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,600
You're still here?

369
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,640
I don't have any charges to file. Go home.

370
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:46,360
Officer, here's the thing.

371
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,960
Actually, we're guilty.

372
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,480
Can we stay one more night, please?

373
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:53,520
This is a jail, not a hotel.

374
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:56,200
Go home already.
You're giving me a headache!

375
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,840
The Goddess.

376
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:15,400
- What?
- I'm connected.

377
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,760
Whoa! The Goddess has arrived!

378
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:20,680
You! You insult me.

379
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,120
You disrespect me.

380
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,600
You're dead!

381
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:28,800
The Goddess has arrived!

382
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:31,520
The Goddess has arrived!

383
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:38,240
It's actually kinda nice here.

384
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:44,120
I just…

385
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:49,160
- So relaxing. Gao.
- Yeah?

386
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:52,200
Gao, tell us a bedtime story.

387
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:31,440
Hello, customer. Your payment's due.

388
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,400
I don't have the money.

389
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:36,360
Oh? Breaking your promise like that…

390
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,960
<i>That's not very nice.</i>

391
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:42,440
I really don't have it this time.
I'll pay double next time.

392
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:45,600
Alright.

393
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:47,400
Come meet me tonight.

394
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,360
<i>I'll send the location.</i>

395
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,360
<i>And if you're thinking of running,</i>

396
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:55,320
don't think we won't find you.

397
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:27,160
<i>Attention passengers</i>
<i>traveling on Express Train No. 109.</i>

398
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:29,640
Risa, I promise.

399
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:33,400
Soon our lives are going to get better.

400
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:37,880
Yes.

401
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:11,280
- Does it hurt a lot?
- It hurts a little.

402
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:14,720
I'll go get you some painkillers.

403
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,280
Okay.

404
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,560
Risa, I have something for you.

405
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:28,280
I made this knife myself.

406
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:30,560
Here. I want you to keep it.

407
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,480
Wait here for me. I'll be right back.

408
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:07,920
<i>Attention passengers</i>
<i>traveling on Express Train No. 109,</i>

409
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,920
<i>please board now.</i>

410
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:40,320
Sorry.

411
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:58,400
Dad!

412
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:04,680
Dad!

413
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:07,560
Dad!

414
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:30,200
Where will you be traveling today, miss?

415
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:33,720
Yeah?

416
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:39,400
Gao, what do you think?

417
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:42,560
Being in here isn't so bad. Free food,

418
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:45,120
and I've been coming up
with all kinds of great ideas.

419
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:48,480
Better than going outside
and running into Kluay.

420
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:51,400
- That's why we are here. Here we go.
- Gotcha!

421
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,080
Cheater!

422
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,240
Some things never change.

423
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,880
Keep it down.

424
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:04,080
I'm trying to think about that Risa girl.

425
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:08,240
Well…

426
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:12,440
Looks like everyone's
having fun and relaxing.

427
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:15,400
You can go now. Someone bailed you out.

428
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:20,320
And this time,
don't cause trouble for the police again.

429
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,440
I'm bruised all over.

430
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:25,080
Wait, Officer. Who bailed us out?

431
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:28,200
I don't know. I just know

432
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:30,400
they brought a gift too.

433
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:32,840
- Here.
- What?

434
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,640
Who's that?

435
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:39,960
Who the hell brought bananas? Only three.

436
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:43,320
Fine. I'm hungry anyway.
Let's split them evenly. Here.

437
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:44,840
Wait.

438
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:47,080
- Damn.
- What's wrong?

439
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:48,440
Boss Kluay.

440
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:52,080
- It's Kluay! Boss Kluay!
- Come out now.

441
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:53,680
Hey, wait.

442
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:55,400
Officer, I'm not going out.

443
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:57,320
I don't want to leave.
I want to stay here.

444
00:30:57,400 --> 00:30:58,480
Are you insane?

445
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,800
Everyone else wants out of jail.

446
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:02,280
What's wrong with you people?

447
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,080
Take them out.

448
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:06,280
- Wait. Hold on.
- I'm not going!

449
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:09,960
- Phayak, climb!
- Hey, don't climb.

450
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,320
- Don't pull me!
- Come out now!

451
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,280
A POLICE STATION FOR THE PEOPLE

452
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:15,240
- Let me stay!
- What's wrong with you?

453
00:31:15,320 --> 00:31:17,280
- I want to stay a little longer.
- This is a mess.

454
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:19,880
- Be gentle! I'm a woman!
- The room's still empty.

455
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:21,600
One or two more nights
won't hurt, Officer.

456
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:25,000
We've got real police work to do.
We have no time to play around with you.

457
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:26,560
I can help mop the floors too, sir.

458
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,720
- Right. Officer.
- I'll make them shine.

459
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:31,760
Hello, Hong.

460
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,480
KIAT SAMKOR BOXING CAMP

461
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,520
We're screwed.

462
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:59,360
There's no way out this time, Yak.

463
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:01,880
Look on the bright side.

464
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:05,640
At least the three of us
are together till the end.

465
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,800
Till the end, my ass!

466
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:12,400
- I'm not ready to die!
- Quiet!

467
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,360
Stop talking! Bag their heads!

468
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:15,800
- Yes.
- Yes.

469
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,160
Bag your head!

470
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,880
Just put it on!

471
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,000
I'm about to put one on you.

472
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:23,080
Shut up! Stay quiet!

473
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:28,080
I can't breathe!

474
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:32,640
- Phayak.
- Huh?

475
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,920
You've got some nerve

476
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,480
running off with my money.

477
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:41,480
Hey.

478
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:44,960
Who should I start with?

479
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:46,800
Hey, boss.

480
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:48,480
Calm down, Boss Kluay.

481
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:51,080
We can talk this through.

482
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,920
Yeah, boss.

483
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:54,400
We didn't mess with your money.

484
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:57,440
There's no way we'd skip out.
It's all in your head.

485
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:59,960
Then where's my three million, huh?

486
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:01,960
Boss Kluay, listen.

487
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:04,320
We managed to gather
the money to pay you back.

488
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:07,320
But some brat came out of nowhere
and snatched it all.

489
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,720
What were we supposed to do?

490
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:12,360
Send the line in, now.

491
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:14,560
- Hey, boss!
- Boss, wait!

492
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:15,920
- Calm down!
- Boss!

493
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,280
Give me one more chance.

494
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:18,760
I'll get the money back to you.

495
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:21,240
- Please give me a chance.
- You still want a chance?

496
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,160
- Yeah.
- How many chances have I given you?

497
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,560
- How many times?
- Five.

498
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,280
Chop off all their legs!

499
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:32,120
- Hey, boss!
- Hey, don't!

500
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:35,240
- Don't do it!
- Boss, stop!

501
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:36,760
I'm telling you to stop!

502
00:33:37,880 --> 00:33:40,440
Boss, think about it.

503
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:43,640
If we lose our legs,
who's going to pay you back?

504
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:45,760
Don't worry about that.

505
00:33:45,840 --> 00:33:47,960
If you lose your legs,

506
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:51,760
I'll make you sit under the overpass

507
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:53,640
and beg

508
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:56,720
until you earn enough to pay me back.
Understand?

509
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:58,760
You're really bad.

510
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:02,320
I think we should start
with this brat first.

511
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:04,920
- Hey
- Quick! Cut!

512
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,560
- Hey, don't do this!
- Boss!

513
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:08,080
- I told you,
- Boss, don't do it!

514
00:34:08,159 --> 00:34:09,760
- I'll pay it back.
- Don't touch Hong!

515
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,920
- Hey!
- Don't touch Hong!

516
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,320
- Cut my legs!
- Boss!

517
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,520
- Boss!
- Cut!

518
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:15,880
- Hey!
- No!

519
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:18,080
- No!
- Don't!

520
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,600
Hey! Stop!

521
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,760
- What is it?
- My mom's calling.

522
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:36,520
Hello, Mom. Yes, it's me.

523
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,440
We'll be fine.

524
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:40,080
I was planning to come see you
in a day or two.

525
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:43,679
Mom, I haven't sinned at all,
never done anything bad.

526
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:47,000
Mom!

527
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:49,960
- Mom!
- Hey, Mom!

528
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,760
Nothing, Mom. Just some noise
from the neighbor lady.

529
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:01,400
I know it's my unlucky year.

530
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:05,280
Huh? Am I going to have bad luck too?

531
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:09,160
Mom, it's just superstitious stuff.
Nothing serious.

532
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:14,800
Yes, I always do as you say.
Right now, I'm at the temple making merit.

533
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,000
Sound, turn it on, quick.

534
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:23,760
Mom, can you hear?

535
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:26,520
I'm really at the temple. I'm not lying.

536
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:28,560
I promise, Mom.

537
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:30,000
I won't kill animals

538
00:35:30,600 --> 00:35:32,560
or take lives, Mom.

539
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:34,480
- Okay, Mom?
- Let me go!

540
00:35:34,560 --> 00:35:37,080
Love you, Mom. Bye.

541
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,600
Let me go!

542
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:46,120
Boss, you have to listen to your mom.

543
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:48,160
She loves you, you know.

544
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:51,680
Boss, being ungrateful,

545
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:54,200
you'll go straight to hell.

546
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:57,960
Boss, just one week, okay?
I'll pay back three…

547
00:35:58,040 --> 00:35:59,280
Four million.

548
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:01,960
I'll pay you four million.

549
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:03,080
Hong.

550
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:07,480
You're very lucky

551
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:10,120
my mom called to intervene. Otherwise,

552
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:11,640
you'd all be screwed.

553
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:14,360
You've got five days
to pay back four million,

554
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:16,480
just like you said.

555
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:19,560
If not, I'll saw off
every one of your legs.

556
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:34,800
Don't think that slipping money
under the table or paying bribes

557
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:36,600
will solve the problem.

558
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:39,880
If we start plugging leaks with money,

559
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:42,560
new leaks will keep popping up.

560
00:36:42,640 --> 00:36:45,360
But the import tax is massive, Pa.

561
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,320
There's just so much of it.

562
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:49,720
I'll cover five million, then.

563
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:52,400
Thank you, Pa.

564
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:56,960
But Shin, you need to show me
your business plan, okay?

565
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,000
Okay.

566
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:04,280
Pa, what about me?
I want to open a store too,

567
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:06,280
a clothing business with my senior.

568
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,680
And I've already done my business plan.

569
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,880
Your brother's serious.
Moei, is this really necessary?

570
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,600
Alright, go ahead.

571
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:16,920
I'll invest too.

572
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:20,440
Really, Pa? I love you the most.

573
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:23,040
Can I borrow some money from you too, Pa?

574
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:30,680
Seeing your siblings invest,
now you want in too?

575
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:34,840
What do you want to do,
and how much capital do you need?

576
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:37,600
Ten million.

577
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:45,680
I just scolded your sister.
Why are you joking around too?

578
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:46,920
I'm serious.

579
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:50,600
You still haven't stopped
talking nonsense, huh?

580
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:53,320
What exactly do you want
to invest that much money in?

581
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:58,960
Honestly, I just want to use the money
to help some friends in trouble.

582
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,120
Losing bets?

583
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:04,440
Or is it loan shark debt?

584
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:07,720
If it's that, I can't give you the money.

585
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,800
How do you even choose your friends?

586
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:13,120
You haven't even graduated yet,
and you're already in debt this deep?

587
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:15,280
People don't all start
with the same opportunities.

588
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:17,920
And they don't have
a rich father like you.

589
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:27,240
Mungkorn, let me teach you something.
It's not about fate.

590
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:30,520
It's about whether people
just sat around doing nothing.

591
00:38:30,600 --> 00:38:33,080
Sure, an old beggar looks pitiful,

592
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:36,320
but what did they do
with their younger years?

593
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:40,080
If they had worked hard
instead of living recklessly,

594
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:42,440
they wouldn't be struggling like this now.

595
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:47,360
But I've always seen you taking pictures
with elderly people at charity events.

596
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:50,680
Oh, is that
just another kind of investment?

597
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:54,240
Are you lecturing me now, huh?

598
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:58,400
- No, I'm just--
- Just what?

599
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:01,040
Just a rich kid

600
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:05,360
pretending to care
about social inequality, huh?

601
00:39:08,240 --> 00:39:09,280
I'll excuse myself now.

602
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:30,880
MUNGKORN

603
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,120
Hey, what's up?

604
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,560
Where are you? In your room?

605
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,320
<i>Yeah.</i>

606
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:42,160
Can I come in?
I've got something to talk to you about.

607
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:46,600
It's not really a good time.

608
00:39:47,640 --> 00:39:48,880
Let's talk later.

609
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:01,000
You're okay, right?

610
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:04,640
I'm fine. I'm okay.

611
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:07,000
<i>Every time you say you're okay,</i>

612
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,960
it feels like you're hiding something.

613
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,640
I really am okay.

614
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:14,680
If that's all,

615
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:16,280
I'm gonna leave it there. I want to sleep.

616
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:19,560
Pao already found him.

617
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:24,080
The guy pretending to be a cop
who stole our money.

618
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:26,560
<i>He's on his trail.</i>

619
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:36,480
KIAT SAMKOR BOXING CAMP

620
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:39,400
Get down!

621
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:41,280
- Just tell me nicely!
- Hey! Hong!

622
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:43,520
- Hey, don't!
- Hong! Don't hurt my friend!

623
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,800
It hurts!

624
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:49,360
Hong! Are you okay?

625
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:50,600
Hong!

626
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:55,720
We made it!

627
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:58,680
I say we figure out a way
to get out of here fast.

628
00:40:58,760 --> 00:41:00,760
Yeah, but where?

629
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,920
We can't go back to the office. Hey.

630
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,200
We could go back to the station,

631
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:06,920
bite a cop's ear,
and spend another two nights in jail.

632
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,960
- Gao!
- No!

633
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:10,840
I mean we need to run,

634
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:12,840
get out of Kluay's reach.

635
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:16,120
- Then where do we go?
- Think! Come on. Help me think!

636
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:18,480
- I've got nothing.
- Stop arguing!

637
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:21,560
We're not running anywhere.

638
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:25,600
The only thing we need to do

639
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:28,000
is track down Risa

640
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:30,960
and get our money back.

641
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:34,840
You're fierce, tiger girl.

642
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,200
Hey, Chiu.

643
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,840
You're Phayak?

644
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,560
Oh, a handshake.

645
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:13,440
Fine, man, bro.

646
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:17,880
Hey, I've got something
I need your help with.

647
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:21,640
Can you help me
look up someone's background?

648
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:26,840
But that's against regulations.

649
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:32,800
I know you can.

650
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:35,680
Let me think.

651
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:40,640
Think.

652
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:42,160
PACKAGE ROOM

653
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:43,400
DOCUMENT STORAGE

654
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:48,640
- Yak.
- Yeah?

655
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:50,280
You really oversold this.

656
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:52,160
Your friend's just working in records.

657
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:54,320
He's just running a name search.

658
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,200
Do you have a better method?

659
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:58,080
Come on, you checked

660
00:42:58,160 --> 00:43:00,120
with the modeling agency Risa works for

661
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:02,800
and gotten fake info.
I didn't even bring that up.

662
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:03,960
- Playing dirty, huh?
- Okay.

663
00:43:04,040 --> 00:43:06,160
- It's ready.
- Alright, ready.

664
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:07,480
This computer

665
00:43:07,560 --> 00:43:10,760
is connected to the central registry.

666
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:15,040
As long as we know
the real first and last name,

667
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,880
whether they're alive

668
00:43:16,960 --> 00:43:18,720
or dead,

669
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,760
we can find them.

670
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:22,640
Turn it on already.

671
00:43:27,960 --> 00:43:29,240
It's coming.

672
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:33,000
It's coming.

673
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:38,600
One, two, three.

674
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:42,000
Not yet. Wait.

675
00:43:42,080 --> 00:43:43,680
Wait. There it is.

676
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:47,720
One.

677
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:49,120
Hang in there.

678
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:51,080
- Two.
- Hang in there.

679
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:54,080
Three.

680
00:43:56,720 --> 00:43:58,000
I'm starting to lose my patience.

681
00:43:58,080 --> 00:43:59,320
Hey!

682
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:01,760
Just turning on the computer
has already taken half the day.

683
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:05,840
By the way, is this computer even working?

684
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:07,600
Don't worry.

685
00:44:07,680 --> 00:44:11,560
If it doesn't, just keep pressing

686
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:13,800
- F1 here.
- Yeah.

687
00:44:13,880 --> 00:44:16,000
And Enter alternately.

688
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:19,120
Eventually, it'll work.

689
00:44:19,720 --> 00:44:23,520
Go ahead, take your time looking.
I'm off to work.

690
00:44:23,600 --> 00:44:24,960
Alright, thanks a lot.

691
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:38,200
Who is it?

692
00:44:39,080 --> 00:44:41,640
Wow, you got beaten this badly?

693
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:43,880
I'm asking who it is.

694
00:44:46,880 --> 00:44:49,600
If that guy stole the phone
we used for the transfer,

695
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:51,520
then he must know our plan, right?

696
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:55,200
And we didn't discuss it anywhere except…

697
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:58,440
- At the internet cafe.
- Yeah, the internet cafe.

698
00:44:59,120 --> 00:45:01,320
So I secretly copied the files.
Check this out.

699
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:06,920
Here he is.

700
00:45:11,160 --> 00:45:12,480
He's been eavesdropping on us.

701
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:30,680
I've already checked his background.

702
00:45:31,880 --> 00:45:35,160
That's Koh, Captain Kongkiat Kamnerdrat.

703
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:38,920
He's a dirty cop, running extortion
schemes at gambling dens and bars,

704
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:42,080
climbing the ranks through favors
with his boss. Eventually, he got caught

705
00:45:42,160 --> 00:45:45,120
in a money laundering and misconduct case

706
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:47,160
and was sentenced to five years.
The moment he got out,

707
00:45:47,240 --> 00:45:49,280
he became a con artist.

708
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:51,000
How are we supposed to track him down?

709
00:45:51,080 --> 00:45:52,840
I checked the vehicle registration,

710
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:55,520
but couldn't find anything.
He's using a fake plate.

711
00:45:57,360 --> 00:46:00,400
Pao, check the CCTV
from the front of the shop.

712
00:46:02,720 --> 00:46:04,360
Zoom in on the sticker on the back.

713
00:46:06,440 --> 00:46:07,920
Z Sound?

714
00:46:08,520 --> 00:46:10,640
Is that the shop
that did the audio install?

715
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:15,160
We should be able to get his number
through this shop.

716
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:18,760
Whoa, genius. You're amazing, man.

717
00:46:18,840 --> 00:46:20,160
Alright, I'll get the number.

718
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:30,760
Yes, it's a black 2022 Porsche Cayenne.

719
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:33,840
I want to buy it, but I don't know how
to contact the owner.

720
00:46:33,920 --> 00:46:37,520
I noticed a Z Sound sticker
on the rear window,

721
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:39,040
so I'm calling to see

722
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:41,840
if the shop has the owner's contact info.

723
00:46:41,920 --> 00:46:44,560
<i>Alright, I'll call them first.</i>

724
00:46:44,640 --> 00:46:47,840
<i>If they're interested,</i>
<i>I'll have them call you back.</i>

725
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:49,960
<i>I'll use the number you're calling from.</i>

726
00:46:50,040 --> 00:46:53,440
Yes, and please tell them
I really want it.

727
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:55,400
I'll pay whatever it takes.

728
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:56,840
<i>Sure, no problem.</i>

729
00:46:56,920 --> 00:46:58,080
Thank you so much.

730
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:03,360
Now we just wait for them to call back.

731
00:47:04,560 --> 00:47:08,040
But in the meantime,
should we drive around and grab some food?

732
00:47:08,120 --> 00:47:09,200
I'm starving.

733
00:47:10,360 --> 00:47:12,520
CENTRAL CIVIL REGISTRY OFFICE

734
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:15,560
Why are there so many people named Risa?

735
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:17,680
I don't know
if it'll take forever to find her.

736
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:19,120
We've been looking for ages.

737
00:47:19,200 --> 00:47:22,440
We don't even know
if her name is really Risa,

738
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:24,120
or if she even exists.

739
00:47:26,920 --> 00:47:28,360
- I'm hungry.
- Come on, let's go.

740
00:47:29,160 --> 00:47:30,040
Yeah.

741
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:32,120
Let's get something to eat.

742
00:47:34,160 --> 00:47:35,240
Sorry, Grandpa.

743
00:47:38,200 --> 00:47:39,280
That brat called me grandpa.

744
00:47:39,360 --> 00:47:41,800
- He called me grandpa.
- Yeah.

745
00:47:44,600 --> 00:47:45,600
What do you have here?

746
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:47,560
Hey.

747
00:47:47,640 --> 00:47:48,520
Grilled pork and grilled liver.

748
00:47:48,600 --> 00:47:50,560
Oh wow, I'll take the grilled pork.

749
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:54,840
- Give me 50 baht's worth.
- Come here.

750
00:47:54,920 --> 00:47:56,840
- What?
- Check this out! Over there!

751
00:47:57,800 --> 00:48:00,200
- What?
- Why does that girl look so familiar?

752
00:48:00,280 --> 00:48:01,960
- Which one?
- That one.

753
00:48:15,680 --> 00:48:17,200
INCOMING CALL

754
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:23,200
Hello.

755
00:48:27,840 --> 00:48:28,720
Hello.

756
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:31,640
Are you the one looking to buy my car?

757
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:33,840
Yes. It matches

758
00:48:33,920 --> 00:48:37,640
exactly what my fortune teller
recommended,

759
00:48:37,720 --> 00:48:41,880
and the license plate is auspicious too.
That's why I want it.

760
00:48:41,960 --> 00:48:44,000
How much are you asking for it?

761
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:46,680
Honestly,

762
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:47,880
I'm not really looking to sell.

763
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:49,320
Whatever it takes, I'll buy it.

764
00:48:50,160 --> 00:48:52,840
<i>I've been looking for a car like this</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

765
00:48:52,920 --> 00:48:55,960
I've never seen a car
that fits this perfectly.

766
00:48:58,520 --> 00:49:01,440
Then ten million,

767
00:49:01,520 --> 00:49:03,080
including the license plate.

768
00:49:03,160 --> 00:49:04,560
I'll take it.

769
00:49:05,760 --> 00:49:09,200
Are you free today?
I'd like to see the car

770
00:49:09,280 --> 00:49:11,920
and put down a deposit.

771
00:49:12,560 --> 00:49:16,360
Alright, let's say 2 p.m.
I'll send the location.

772
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:17,800
Okay.

773
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:27,280
Hello, customer.

774
00:49:29,240 --> 00:49:30,280
Hey, buddy.

775
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:35,320
Wow, you're smiling so big.
What's got you so happy?

776
00:49:36,560 --> 00:49:38,400
I just bought a car for seven million,

777
00:49:38,480 --> 00:49:40,520
and someone's offering ten million
to buy it.

778
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:42,520
Wow, my luck is on fire.

779
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:44,920
He really drives a hard bargain.

780
00:49:45,880 --> 00:49:47,960
This guy's evil in every way.

781
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:50,520
He's about to get what's coming to him.

782
00:49:56,080 --> 00:49:57,160
Let me see.

783
00:49:58,960 --> 00:50:00,400
You're selling just one car.

784
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:03,200
That's like me having to run
my cafe for ten years.

785
00:50:03,280 --> 00:50:04,520
Come on.

786
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:07,680
Don't get discouraged.
We just started the business.

787
00:50:07,760 --> 00:50:09,200
Trust me, it'll pick up soon.

788
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:11,640
It's because I trusted you

789
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:16,120
that the shop's been so dead.
Not a single customer in sight.

790
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:22,680
There's their car.

791
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:32,240
Angpao, can you hack their CCTV?

792
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:33,440
Give me a second.

793
00:50:43,080 --> 00:50:44,000
Let's see.

794
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:49,960
Easy.

795
00:50:52,160 --> 00:50:54,080
It's a CCTV system
connected through Wi-Fi.

796
00:50:54,160 --> 00:50:56,120
We just break in through the DVR

797
00:50:56,200 --> 00:50:58,720
or access the cloud linked to the phone.

798
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:02,000
Done. Let's spy on them.

799
00:51:14,920 --> 00:51:16,080
What are you doing?

800
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:19,560
<i>Once I sell the car</i>
<i>I'm going to celebrate</i>

801
00:51:19,640 --> 00:51:22,160
<i>Can I borrow like a hundred grand?</i>

802
00:51:22,240 --> 00:51:25,120
<i>Nope, not giving it</i>
<i>Even if I had it, you're not getting it</i>

803
00:51:25,200 --> 00:51:27,480
<i>Go take money from your safe</i>

804
00:51:27,560 --> 00:51:31,000
<i>Wanna go out? Go racing?</i>

805
00:51:31,080 --> 00:51:33,080
<i>Shouldn't we wait until the shop closes?</i>

806
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:36,440
<i>Ugh, I can't wait</i>
<i>We'll be too late</i>

807
00:51:36,520 --> 00:51:38,480
<i>Then we're not going</i>
<i>You idiot!</i>

808
00:51:38,560 --> 00:51:41,000
- Hey!
- Hey, what?

809
00:51:56,840 --> 00:51:58,880
- Is there a camera in the back?
- Yes.

810
00:52:20,040 --> 00:52:22,200
There it is. Our money's right there.

811
00:52:22,880 --> 00:52:25,560
But how do we get it?

812
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:28,760
Let's lure Koh out first.

813
00:52:29,360 --> 00:52:31,800
If only the big guy's left, we can get in.

814
00:52:42,240 --> 00:52:44,680
Hello. Did you get the right place?

815
00:52:44,760 --> 00:52:46,080
I'm on my way,

816
00:52:46,160 --> 00:52:49,800
but traffic's terrible.
Can you meet me halfway?

817
00:52:51,960 --> 00:52:53,040
Another day works too.

818
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:56,440
Well, I'm flying abroad tomorrow.

819
00:52:56,520 --> 00:52:58,720
<i>So I want to reserve it in advance.</i>

820
00:53:01,160 --> 00:53:04,400
Alright, but a 30% deposit
is required today.

821
00:53:04,480 --> 00:53:07,880
No problem. I'll share
the location right now.

822
00:53:07,960 --> 00:53:08,960
<i>Okay.</i>

823
00:53:11,680 --> 00:53:14,160
Get ready to move in.
That jerk's about to leave.

824
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,360
- Hey, wait a sec.
- Awesome.

825
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:20,600
What are you doing?

826
00:53:20,680 --> 00:53:23,000
I'm putting a GPS tracker on his car.

827
00:53:23,080 --> 00:53:24,920
That way, we'll know when he comes back.

828
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:28,400
They'll be gone if you go.
Let me handle it.

829
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:14,600
Hey, Chen.

830
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:17,200
When you're done, follow me.

831
00:54:17,280 --> 00:54:19,440
Yeah, you'll see when I get there.

832
00:54:35,680 --> 00:54:37,560
Hey, take it easy, man.

833
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:41,640
You're driving too fast.

834
00:54:55,600 --> 00:54:56,680
Awesome, Mung.

835
00:55:01,800 --> 00:55:02,640
All clear.

836
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:05,680
Risa.

837
00:55:07,320 --> 00:55:09,000
Let's go get our money back.

838
00:55:12,640 --> 00:55:14,680
Oh, hello.

839
00:55:17,040 --> 00:55:18,920
Welcome to Cocoa Cafe.

840
00:55:40,840 --> 00:55:42,080
Got any recommendations?

841
00:55:42,160 --> 00:55:44,720
Our specials are mango honey toast,

842
00:55:44,800 --> 00:55:47,560
red velvet pancakes,
and raspberry crème brûlée.

843
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:49,000
- As for drinks--
- Then I'll have

844
00:55:50,040 --> 00:55:51,520
a glass of whiskey.

845
00:55:53,720 --> 00:55:55,120
Sorry, sir.

846
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:57,840
This is a dessert cafe.
We don't serve alcohol.

847
00:55:57,920 --> 00:56:01,000
Oh, is that so?
Do you have anything that's not sweet?

848
00:56:01,080 --> 00:56:04,040
No, this is a dessert cafe.

849
00:56:04,120 --> 00:56:06,480
But I don't like sweets.

850
00:56:06,560 --> 00:56:10,160
Then why'd you come in?

851
00:56:27,640 --> 00:56:29,200
Stop acting.

852
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:31,400
I know what you two are up to.

853
00:56:31,480 --> 00:56:33,960
- Finally found you, you brat.
- Where's my friend?

854
00:56:34,040 --> 00:56:37,240
You can't trick us again. This time,

855
00:56:37,320 --> 00:56:38,880
you're done for.

856
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:39,800
The cops are coming!

857
00:56:39,880 --> 00:56:41,000
You crazy boy!

858
00:56:41,080 --> 00:56:42,800
Why did you trick me?

859
00:56:42,880 --> 00:56:44,240
That's his weakness.

860
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:47,560
<i>If he loves his mom this much,</i>
<i>we'll grab her.</i>

861
00:56:47,640 --> 00:56:49,760
- <i>Make him pay to get her back.</i>
- Hey! Stop!

862
00:56:49,840 --> 00:56:52,080
<i>Right now, your mom's with me.</i>

863
00:56:52,160 --> 00:56:54,440
<i>If you want her released,</i>

864
00:56:54,520 --> 00:56:57,760
<i>bring ten million for the exchange.</i>

865
00:56:57,840 --> 00:56:59,480
If you don't, I'll shoot.

866
00:57:47,960 --> 00:57:50,440
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
